  Disjoint
  (@card (rootSet (derivative p) ℂ) (rootSetFintype (derivative p) ℂ))
  (@card (rootSet p ℂ) (rootSetFintype p ℂ)) :=

records.nl_statement: Show that X is countably compact if and only if every nested sequence $C_1 \supset C_2 \supset \cdots$ of closed nonempty sets of X has a nonempty intersection.

def countably_compact (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] :=
  ∀ U : ℕ → Set X,
  (∀ i, IsOpen (U i)) ∧ ((univ : Set X) ⊆ ⋃ i, U i) →
  (∃ t : Finset ℕ, (univ : Set X) ⊆ ⋃ i ∈ t, U i)
